IMGEMI-COMBO - DNA & RNA isolation

2025-10-19





All 67 samples from NIO-PIB underwent isolation, including 47 tumor tissue samples and 20 paired healthy control samples (for WES germline variant subtraction).

Tumor tissue

Yellow line - 500ng - DNA quantity allowing for exectuion of RRBS (methylation profiling) and WES with a safety margin - achieved in 41 (87.2%) samples

Orange line - 260ng - DNA quantity required for RRBS (10ng) plus recommended to perform WES (250ng) - achieved in 45 (95.7%) samples

Red line - 60ng - technical minimum needed to perform RRBS (10ng) and WES (50ng) - achieved in 47 (100%) samples







Healthy control

Orange line - 250ng - DNA quantity recommended to perform WES - achieved in 6 (30%) samples

Red line - 50ng - technical minimum needed to perform WES - achieved in 16 (80%) samples

RNA samples with concentration below detection range were set to 0.1 ng
